[32mSlow Pion Efficiency[0m
====================

[1;36mDescription[0m
-----------
accounts for the different reconstruction efficiency in data and in MC. Efficiency correction for low-momentum tracks, to be applied on MC. The correction is provided separately for Run1 and Run2.
The per-track-correction should be applied according to the track momentum, the track momentum range between 50 and 200 MeV/c is split in three bins. For each bin the following quantities are provided: central value and three uncertainties (stat uncorrelated, stat correlated, systematics).
The central value is the correction to be applied to the MC efficiency to better reproduce the efficiency on data, the uncertainties should be used to evaluate the systematic impact of the correction on your observable.
To evaluate the systematic uncertainty due to the correction you should evaluate two contributions, one is uncorrelated among momentum bins (1) and the other is correlated among momentum bins (2):
(1): estimate the impact on your observable with ToyMC, varying the central value of the correction in each bin by randomly drawing from a gaussian with mean = central_value and width = stat_uncorr;
(2): vary the central_value of the correction by +-1sigma at the same time in all bins and see how the central value of your observable changes.
The total systematic uncertainty is the sum in quadrature of what obtained in (1) and (2)

[1;36mRecommendation[0m
--------------
+ **[1mbinning[0m** - The track momentum range between 50 and 200 MeV/c is split in three bins: (1) 0.05 < p < 0.12 GeV, (2) 0.12-0.16 GeV, (3) 0.16-0.20 GeV
+ **[1mcorrections Run1 and Run2[0m** - https://gitlab.desy.de/belle2/performance/correction-tables/-/tree/main/MC16/tracking/slow-pion?ref_type=heads
