[32mDifferential Track Momentum Scale and Energy Loss Corrections[0m
=============================================================

[1;36mDescription[0m
-----------
Imperfections in the B-field map and in the detector material description on basf2 require (small) corrections for the track momenta and the energy loss of the track in the material. We provide polar-angle-dependent corrections for the track momentum, and momentum-dependent energy-loss corrections for Run1 and Run2 2025 data and run-dependent MC16rd (see BELLE2-NOTE-PH-2023-069 V7 for full documentation). If your analysis is sensitive to this correction, it is recommended to re-run your analysis twice using the weights "total_up" and  "total_down", respectively, instead of the "central" weight, and assign the difference in the result as systematic uncertainty. Note: The given global tag (GT) is valid for MC and data, as well for both Run1 and Run2 (exp 12 - 26 and exp 30 - 35). Corresponding payloads will be picked automatically, so no need to change the GT. You still need to specify the correct payloads (contained in the GT) depending on if you run over data or MC (also see snippet)!

